<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="541" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,824,1031]" box="[151,1241,824,851]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,415,824,850]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">
Distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[335,410,824,850]" name="China" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">China</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[422,556,824,850]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[567,651,824,850]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Hainan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[661,754,824,850]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
, Taiwan, 
<collectingRegion box="[860,946,825,851]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Huang, F. - S." box="[960,1103,825,851]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" refId="ref31554" refString="Huang, F. - S. (1987) Forest Insects of Yunnan. Yunnan Science and Technology Press, Kunming, 1622 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="1987">Huang 1987</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hua, L. - Z." box="[1114,1229,825,851]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" refId="ref31518" refString="Hua, L. - Z. (2002) List of Chinese Insects. Vol. II. Zhongshan (Sun Yat-sen) University Press, Guangzhou, 612 pp. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2002">Hua 2002</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,824,1031]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,428,860,886]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Other distribution.</emphasis>
South and Southeast Asia from 
<collectingCountry box="[803,861,860,886]" name="India" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">India</collectingCountry>
to the Indonesian archipelago, Arabian peninsula, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,286,896,922]" name="Madagascar" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ocean" authorityName="Ocean" box="[341,491,896,923]" class="Aves" family="Phasianidae" genus="Indian" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Galliformes" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Indian Ocean</taxonomicName>
islands. Introduced to Europe and North America (
<bibRefCitation author="Beaver, R. &amp; Sittichaya, W. &amp; Liu, L. - Y." box="[1064,1275,896,923]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" pagination="135 - 158" refId="ref30546" refString="Beaver, R., Sittichaya, W. &amp; Liu, L. - Y. (2011) A Review of the Powder-Post Beetles of Thailand (Coleoptera: Bostrichidae). Tropical Natural History, 11 (2), 135 - 158." type="journal article" year="2011">
Beaver 
<emphasis box="[1152,1208,896,922]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="541" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,824,1031]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,933,959]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Host plants.</emphasis>
A polyphagous species with many recorded host plants (
<bibRefCitation author="Beeson, C. F. C. &amp; Bhatia, B. M." box="[1007,1274,932,959]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" pagination="223 - 323" refId="ref30593" refString="Beeson, C. F. C. &amp; Bhatia, B. M. (1937) On the biology of the Bostrychidae (Coleopt.). Indian Forest Records, New Series Entomology, 2, 223 - 323." type="journal article" year="1937">Beeson &amp; Bhatia 1937</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Beaver, R. &amp; Sittichaya, W. &amp; Liu, L. - Y." pageId="40" pageNumber="541" pagination="135 - 158" refId="ref30546" refString="Beaver, R., Sittichaya, W. &amp; Liu, L. - Y. (2011) A Review of the Powder-Post Beetles of Thailand (Coleoptera: Bostrichidae). Tropical Natural History, 11 (2), 135 - 158." type="journal article" year="2011">
Beaver 
<emphasis box="[1377,1429,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
). It is the most abundant species in durian orchards in S. 
<collectingCountry box="[844,944,968,994]" name="Thailand" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sittichaya, W. &amp; Thaochan, N. &amp; Tasen, W." box="[958,1201,968,995]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" pagination="374 - 386" refId="ref33107" refString="Sittichaya, W., Thaochan, N. &amp; Tasen, W. (2013) Powderpost Beetle Communities (Coleoptera: Bostrichidae) in Durian-Based Agricultural Areas in Southern Thailand. Kasetsart Journal - Natural Science, 47, 374 - 386." type="journal article" year="2013">
Sittichaya 
<emphasis box="[1078,1127,968,994]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="541">et al</emphasis>
. 2013
</bibRefCitation>
). The life cycle takes a minimum of three months and there can be 2–3 generations per year (
<bibRefCitation author="Beeson, C. F. C. &amp; Bhatia, B. M." box="[950,1210,1004,1031]" pageId="40" pageNumber="541" pagination="223 - 323" refId="ref30593" refString="Beeson, C. F. C. &amp; Bhatia, B. M. (1937) On the biology of the Bostrychidae (Coleopt.). Indian Forest Records, New Series Entomology, 2, 223 - 323." type="journal article" year="1937">Beeson &amp; Bhatia 1937</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
